WEBVTT

00:03.254 --> 00:06.467
SO, HE'S JUST BACK?

00:06.467 --> 00:08.679
MM.
FOR GOOD?

00:08.679 --> 00:09.720
YEAH.

00:09.720 --> 00:12.053
OKAY, THAT FACE
THAT YOU'RE MAKING --

00:12.053 --> 00:15.096
I DON'T KNOW YOU WELL ENOUGH
TO KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.

00:15.096 --> 00:17.348
YOU KNOW THOSE VERY HAPPY,
CHEERFUL PEOPLE

00:17.348 --> 00:18.769
WHO HAVE EVERYTHING

00:18.769 --> 00:21.442
AND WHEN THE FACT THAT
THEY HAVE EVERYTHING COMES UP,

00:21.442 --> 00:22.643
THEY ACT VERY HUMBLE

00:22.643 --> 00:24.735
AND THEY SAY,
"I'M JUST SO BLESSED."

00:24.735 --> 00:27.908
THOSE PEOPLE -- YOU WANT TO
PUNCH THOSE PEOPLE IN THE FACE.

00:27.908 --> 00:29.910
YES.
I DO KNOW THOSE PEOPLE.

00:29.910 --> 00:31.152
YEAH, I'M ONE
OF THOSE PEOPLE NOW.

00:31.152 --> 00:31.992
OKAY.

00:31.992 --> 00:34.245
THIS MORNING,
I WAS STANDING ON MY PORCH

00:34.245 --> 00:37.208
OF MY PERFECT HOUSE
LOOKING IN THE WINDOW

00:37.208 --> 00:39.210
AT MY AMAZING,
PERFECT CHILDREN

00:39.210 --> 00:41.212
AND MY AMAZING,
GORGEOUS HUSBAND,

00:41.212 --> 00:43.544
ON THE WAY
TO MY AMAZING JOB.

00:43.544 --> 00:47.758
AND I THOUGHT TO MYSELF, "I HAVE
EVERYTHING I'VE EVER WANTED.

00:47.758 --> 00:50.131
I AM JUST SO BLESSED."

00:50.131 --> 00:53.174
I REALLY WANT PUMMEL
YOUR FACE IN RIGHT NOW.

00:53.174 --> 00:54.805
RIGHT,
I WOULD BEAT MYSELF UP.

00:54.805 --> 00:56.347
EXCEPT I'M TOO TIRED
FROM --

00:56.347 --> 00:58.058
WERE YOU ABOUT TO SAY
THAT YOU'RE EXHAUSTED

00:58.058 --> 00:59.770
FROM ALL THE GREAT SEX
YOU'RE HAVING?

00:59.770 --> 01:02.773
I AM JUST SO BLESSED.

01:02.773 --> 01:05.186
I'M GONNA WALK AWAY
FROM YOU NOW.
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

01:05.186 --> 01:06.737
Meredith: PICTURE THE LIFE
YOU DREAMED OF LIVING...

01:06.737 --> 01:08.279
♪ CAN I MOVE LIKE THIS? ♪

01:08.279 --> 01:11.071
♪ BABY, IF YOU MOVE LIKE THAT ♪

01:11.071 --> 01:14.995
...THE PERSON
YOU PICTURED BEING WITH.

01:14.995 --> 01:16.787
PICTURE THE JOB
YOU DREAMED YOU'D HAVE.

01:16.787 --> 01:18.999
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]
I'M A SURGEON HERE
AT GREY-SLOAN,

01:18.999 --> 01:21.502
BUT I LIKE TO THINK OF MYSELF
FIRST AS A TEACHER.

01:21.502 --> 01:23.964
I TRAIN YOUNG DOCTORS
TO BECOME SURGEONS.

01:23.964 --> 01:26.707
ARE YOU LIVING THE LIFE
YOU ENVISIONED FOR YOURSELF?

01:26.707 --> 01:28.969
ARE YOU WHO YOU WANTED TO BE...

01:28.969 --> 01:31.212
YOU GUYS, LET'S GET A PICTURE.
COME ON.

01:34.715 --> 01:37.718
EVERYBODY,
EYES OVER THERE.

01:37.718 --> 01:40.481
ONE, TWO, THREE.

01:40.481 --> 01:41.852
CHEESE!
CHEESE!
CHEESE!
CHEESE!

01:41.852 --> 01:42.853
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

01:42.853 --> 01:44.145
...WHEN YOU GREW UP?

01:44.145 --> 01:45.606
I HAVE SOME LOOSE ENDS
IN D.C.,

01:45.606 --> 01:47.568
SO I'LL BE FLYING BACK AND FORTH
FOR A FEW WEEKS.

01:47.568 --> 01:49.990
TIE THEM UP, HAND THEM OFF,
AND THEN I'LL BE HERE FOR GOOD.

01:49.990 --> 01:51.402
AND YOU WANT
TO COME BACK FULL-TIME?

01:51.402 --> 01:53.113
THAT'S THE PLAN.
THIS IS GREAT.

01:53.113 --> 01:55.156
UH, YOU REALIZE ALL THIS
HAS TO BE APPROVED?

01:55.156 --> 01:55.996
BY WHOM?

01:55.996 --> 01:57.618
I'M ON THE BOARD.
I HAVE PRIVILEGES.

01:57.618 --> 01:59.200
BY AMELIA.

01:59.200 --> 02:02.623
OF COURSE.
I'LL ASK AMELIA.

02:02.623 --> 02:05.416
I AM THE HEAD OF THE DEPARTMENT
OF NEUROSURGERY,

02:05.416 --> 02:09.510
AND THAT MEANS
I OPERATE ON...BRAINS.

02:09.510 --> 02:11.672
COOL!
COOL!
COOL!

02:11.672 --> 02:13.424
IT'S VERY COOL,
ACTUALLY,

02:13.424 --> 02:16.257
BECAUSE I FIX THE BIG,
SQUISHY, SLIMY COMPUTER

02:16.257 --> 02:18.179
THAT RUNS
YOUR WHOLE BODY.

02:18.179 --> 02:20.721
IF THE BRAIN GOES,
EVERYTHING GOES.

02:20.721 --> 02:22.022
IT IS THE COOLEST.

02:22.022 --> 02:24.064
AND, UH,
THIS IS DR. DEREK SHEPHERD,

02:24.064 --> 02:27.188
AND HE'S A MEMBER OF OUR BOARD,
AND, UM...

02:27.188 --> 02:28.939
I'M HER BROTHER.

02:28.939 --> 02:32.483
I'M ALSO A NEUROSURGEON.
I WORK FOR HER.

02:32.483 --> 02:33.484
YOUR SISTER'S
YOUR BOSS?

02:33.484 --> 02:35.075
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

02:35.075 --> 02:36.237
MY SISTER'S MY BOSS.

02:36.237 --> 02:38.158
OKAY, KIDS, UH,
LET'S KEEP IT MOVING.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.200
UH, THANK YOU,
DOCTORS.

02:39.200 --> 02:40.701
MM-HMM.
MM-HMM. MM-HMM.

02:40.701 --> 02:41.992
OH, SWEET!

02:41.992 --> 02:44.205
HOW HARD WAS THAT
FOR YOU TO SAY?

02:44.205 --> 02:45.206
ROLLS OFF THE TONGUE.

02:45.206 --> 02:47.047
IT'S NOT GONNA BE
LIKE IT WAS BEFORE.

02:47.047 --> 02:48.419
I'M NOT GONNA ANGLE
FOR YOUR JOB.

02:48.419 --> 02:50.791
I'M NOT GONNA STEAL YOUR
PATIENTS. I JUST WANT TO WORK.

02:50.791 --> 02:53.424
YOU SAY THAT NOW,
BUT I KNOW YOU, DEREK.

02:53.424 --> 02:54.675
I KNOW US.

02:54.675 --> 02:56.597
YOU GREW UP
BOSSING ME AROUND.

02:56.597 --> 02:58.679
I -- I DON'T KNOW
THAT THIS CAN WORK.

02:58.679 --> 03:00.761
GIVE ME A CHANCE,
AND I WILL SHOW YOU.

03:00.761 --> 03:01.852
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

03:01.852 --> 03:03.854
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
FOR YOU TODAY.

03:03.854 --> 03:06.397
I-I-I'M CLIPPING
AN ANEURYSM LATER.

03:06.397 --> 03:08.108
I WILL LET YOU KNOW.

03:08.108 --> 03:10.271
YOU'RE NOT GONNA MAKE THIS FUN,
ARE YOU?

03:10.271 --> 03:12.072
IT'S A LOT OF FUN
FOR ME.

03:12.072 --> 03:14.114
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
[ SIGHS ]

03:14.114 --> 03:15.776
Stephanie:
NO, NO, NO.

03:15.776 --> 03:17.077
EW. SUPER NO.

03:17.077 --> 03:19.820
WAIT, NO, HE'S CUTE, I THINK.
YOU'RE GOING SO FAST.

03:19.820 --> 03:22.162
HE'S 32 AND WEARING
A HIGH-SCHOOL LETTERMAN JACKET.

03:22.162 --> 03:23.914
YOUR GLORY DAYS ARE OVER, STEVE.
GIVE IT UP.

03:23.914 --> 03:26.126
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU ARE SO QUICK TO JUDGE.

03:26.126 --> 03:27.127
IT'S A SKILL.

03:27.127 --> 03:28.168
YOU SPEND ENOUGH TIME
ON THIS THING,

03:28.168 --> 03:29.630
YOU CAN LEARN
EVERYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW

03:29.630 --> 03:32.172
FROM THE FIRST PICTURE.

03:32.172 --> 03:33.294
WILL -- CARES TOO MUCH
ABOUT HIS CARS.

03:33.294 --> 03:35.886
HMM.
MIKE -- TOO CLOSE
WITH THOSE CATS.

03:35.886 --> 03:37.888
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
THEO NEEDS TO LEARN
TO WEAR A SHIRT.

03:37.888 --> 03:39.470
[ LAUGHS ]
OKAY, OKAY, THEO IS A NO-GO,

03:39.470 --> 03:41.682
BUT MAYBE YOUR PICKINESS
IS KEEPING YOU

03:41.682 --> 03:43.344
FROM GOING ON
ANY REAL DATES.

03:43.344 --> 03:45.225
YOU NEED TO EXPAND
YOUR HORIZONS.

03:45.225 --> 03:46.517
UGH. [ SIGHS ]

03:46.517 --> 03:50.020
MY HORIZONS HAVEN'T BEEN
EXPANDED IN A VERY LONG TIME.

03:50.020 --> 03:51.191
UGH, GROSS!

03:51.191 --> 03:53.614
I MEAN, YES,
BUT GROSS.

03:53.614 --> 03:54.905
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:54.905 --> 03:57.448
SO, I AM
A PLASTIC SURGEON.

03:57.448 --> 04:00.160
I ALSO OPERATE ON THE EAR,
NOSE, AND THROAT.

04:00.160 --> 04:01.201
THIS IS DR. WARREN.

04:01.201 --> 04:03.414
HE IS A TERRIFIC
SURGICAL RESIDENT.

04:03.414 --> 04:07.037
AND TOGETHER,
WE FORM THE PLASTICS POSSE.

04:07.037 --> 04:08.329
[ LAUGHS ]

04:08.329 --> 04:10.751
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
WELL, HE CALLS US THAT.
YEAH.

04:10.751 --> 04:12.833
BUT, UH, I DO NOT.
AH, IT'S --
IT'S WHAT WE'RE CALLED.

04:12.833 --> 04:14.214
IT'S, YOU KNOW,
WHAT THEY CALL US.

04:14.214 --> 04:16.717
NO, SEE, THEY DON'T THINK
IT'S COOL BECAUSE IT'S NOT.

04:16.717 --> 04:18.969
WELL, IT'S NOT FOR THEM, BEN.
IT'S FOR US, OKAY?

04:18.969 --> 04:20.180
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

04:20.180 --> 04:22.343
ALL RIGHT, KIDS,
LET'S GO CHECK OUT THE E.R.

04:22.343 --> 04:23.884
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO.

04:23.884 --> 04:25.015
MAKING MEDICINE COOL.

04:25.015 --> 04:27.187
HUH? NOT FAMILIAR
WITH THE HIGH-FIVE.

04:27.187 --> 04:28.979
[ SIGHS ] ALL RIGHT.

04:28.979 --> 04:30.270
SO, I HAVE
A TELECONFERENCE ALL DAY,

04:30.270 --> 04:31.482
SO YOU CAN HOLD
DOWN THE FORT FOR ME?

04:31.482 --> 04:32.523
BUT I'M NOT
ON YOUR SERVICE TODAY.

04:32.523 --> 04:34.525
YOU'RE ALWAYS
ON MY SERVICE.

04:34.525 --> 04:36.567
[ SCOFFS ]
AT LEAST IN SPIRIT.
CAN I HEAR IT?

04:36.567 --> 04:37.858
ONCE?
YOU WANT TO SAY IT?

04:37.858 --> 04:39.069
[ LAUGHS ] NO.

04:39.069 --> 04:41.612
NO?
THINKING ABOUT IT?
NOPE!

04:41.612 --> 04:42.993
PLASTICS POSSE.

04:42.993 --> 04:44.615
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

04:44.615 --> 04:48.208
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:48.208 --> 04:49.670
UH, EX-EXCUSE ME.
YEAH?

04:49.670 --> 04:51.211
I LOST TRACK OF MY KIDS.

04:51.211 --> 04:52.833
AND I...
YOUR KIDS?

04:52.833 --> 04:55.085
10 OF THEM, FIFTH GRADERS,
VARYING HEIGHTS.

04:55.085 --> 04:56.216
OH, THE FIELD TRIP.

04:56.216 --> 04:57.508
YEAH, I WENT TO THE RESTROOM,
AND I CAME OUT,

04:57.508 --> 04:58.879
AND THEY'D VANISHED,
SO I...

04:58.879 --> 05:01.552
YOU'RE A TERRIBLE CHAPERONE
IS WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

05:01.552 --> 05:02.843
[ SIGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:02.843 --> 05:04.425
THAT'S WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE,
YEAH.

05:04.425 --> 05:07.057
[ LAUGHS ] I THINK THEY'RE
WITH DR. WEBBER IN THE
EMERGENCY ROOM.

05:07.057 --> 05:09.139
YOU DON'T, UH, HAPPEN TO KNOW
WHERE THAT IS, DO YOU?

05:09.139 --> 05:10.691
I DO.
FOLLOW ME.

05:10.691 --> 05:11.932
OKAY. THANK YOU.

05:11.932 --> 05:13.644
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:13.644 --> 05:15.025
A TRAUMA
IS ANY KIND OF INJURY.

05:15.025 --> 05:17.818
SO, IF YOU CUT YOURSELF OR
YOU BREAK YOUR LEG SKATEBOARDING

05:17.818 --> 05:21.652
OR WRECK YOUR BIKE, ALL OF THOSE
INJURIES ARE CALLED TRAUMAS,

05:21.652 --> 05:23.323
AND THAT'S WHAT WE ARE
SET UP HERE TO TREAT.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.205
[ SIREN WAILING ]
NOW, FOR A LOT OF PEOPLE,

05:25.205 --> 05:27.037
THE EMERGENCY ROOM CAN BE
KIND OF A SCARY PLACE,

05:27.037 --> 05:28.158
BUT IT'S ACTUALLY --

05:28.158 --> 05:29.660
COOL.
COOL.
COOL.

05:29.660 --> 05:31.161
A POLICE CAR!

05:31.161 --> 05:33.624
THE POLICE!
Dan: I NEED SOME HELP
OVER HERE!

05:33.624 --> 05:35.005
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT HERE,
SET HIM DOWN.

05:35.005 --> 05:36.717
KIDS, LET'S MOVE.

05:36.717 --> 05:37.718
WE GOT TWO GUYS DOWN.

05:37.718 --> 05:38.919
WE COULDN'T WAIT
FOR THE MEDICS.

05:38.919 --> 05:40.721
OKAY, I NEED A GURNEY.
TRAUMA ROOM IS IN THERE.

05:40.721 --> 05:42.092
BACK UP.

05:42.092 --> 05:44.054
PAGE GREY, TORRES.
LET'S GET CARDIO IN HERE.

05:44.054 --> 05:46.266
BRETT, THEY GOT YOU NOW, BUDDY.
ALL RIGHT, YOU JUST RELAX.

05:46.266 --> 05:49.099
YOU LET THEM
TAKE CARE OF YOU, OKAY?

05:55.145 --> 05:58.238
IT'S OKAY.
OKAY, LET'S GO.

06:11.542 --> 06:13.293
JUST STICK AGAINST THE WALL
AND LET THE DOCTORS THROUGH.

06:13.293 --> 06:14.755
TO THE SIDE.
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

06:14.755 --> 06:16.296
WHERE ARE THEY GOING?
IS THAT POLICEMAN
GONNA DIE?

06:16.296 --> 06:17.418
ALL RIGHT,
EVERYONE STAY CALM.

06:17.418 --> 06:18.499
EVERYTHING'S OKAY,
ALL RIGHT?

06:18.499 --> 06:19.840
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:19.840 --> 06:22.002
MULTIPLE GUNSHOT WOUNDS FROM
A ROBBERY STILL IN PROGRESS.

06:22.002 --> 06:25.175
SOUNDS LIKE A BLOODBATH.
WHOA -- HI, KIDS.

06:25.175 --> 06:26.557
SORRY.

06:26.557 --> 06:29.139
UH, I SHOULD PROBABLY
GO WITH THEM, RIGHT?

06:29.139 --> 06:30.140
DID YOU GET PAGED?

06:30.140 --> 06:31.311
NO.
THEN NO.

06:31.311 --> 06:32.893
WE SHOULD JUST TAKE THE KIDS
BACK TO THE SCHOOL.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.184
NO, WE CAN'T.

06:34.184 --> 06:35.726
I CAN'T REACH THE BUS DRIVER,
AND HE'S NOT DUE BACK TILL 3:00.

06:35.726 --> 06:37.147
IS THERE SOMEPLACE
THAT WE CAN --

06:37.147 --> 06:38.569
DR. WEBBER,
YOU COMING?

06:38.569 --> 06:40.230
YEAH,
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

06:40.230 --> 06:42.362
UM, KIDS,
LET'S GO SEE THE BABIES.

06:42.362 --> 06:44.194
IT'S NICE AND PEACEFUL
UP THERE.
Woman: EXCUSE ME.

06:44.194 --> 06:45.656
DR. EDWARDS
WILL TAKE YOU.

06:45.656 --> 06:47.197
I WILL?
YEAH, IT'LL BE FINE.

06:47.197 --> 06:48.449
Richard:
MAKE MEDICINE FUN.

06:48.449 --> 06:50.030
EDUCATE, ENTERTAIN, INSPIRE.

06:50.030 --> 06:52.453
AND KEEP THEM AWAY
FROM THE SCARY STUFF.

06:52.453 --> 06:54.164
Dan:
IT WAS A BANK ROBBERY.

06:54.164 --> 06:55.836
THREE SUSPECTS HELD UP
THE BANK TELLERS AT GUNPOINT.

06:55.836 --> 06:57.037
BRETT AND I
MOVED IN FIRST,

06:57.037 --> 06:58.208
BUT AS SOON AS THEY SAW US,
THEY PANICKED.

06:58.208 --> 06:59.419
THEY JUST
STARTED FIRING,

06:59.419 --> 07:01.171
HIT ME RIGHT THROUGH
THE SIDE OF MY VEST.

07:01.171 --> 07:03.253
PETE, TRY NOT
TO MOVE YOUR NECK, OKAY?

07:03.253 --> 07:05.846
WHAT ARE WE LOOKING AT?
Maggie: TWO GUNSHOT WOUNDS
TO THE UPPER-LEFT CHEST CAVITY.

07:05.846 --> 07:07.758
Owen: AT LEAST THREE BULLET
HOLES IN HIS LEFT ABDOMEN.

07:07.758 --> 07:09.009
Richard:
I'M GONNA NEED ACCESS.

07:09.009 --> 07:10.260
HERE, I'M GONNA START
A SUBCLAVIAN LINE.

07:10.260 --> 07:11.812
[ Strained ] HAVE THEY
BROUGHT BRETT IN YET?

07:11.812 --> 07:14.054
HE'S BEING WORKED ON
RIGHT NEXT DOOR.
IS HE OKAY?

07:14.054 --> 07:16.186
HE TOOK THE BRUNT OF IT.
Dan: TWO OF THEM
WERE ARMED.

07:16.186 --> 07:18.228
BRETT TOOK ONE OF THEM DOWN,
THEN HE GRABBED THE OTHER ONE.

07:18.228 --> 07:19.820
HE ENDED THE THING,
EVEN AFTER HE WAS HIT.

07:19.820 --> 07:21.822
HE'S THE ONLY REASON
I'M STANDING HERE RIGHT NOW.

07:21.822 --> 07:23.153
BRETT SAVED IT.

07:24.024 --> 07:26.987
BLOOD'S FILLING HIS
CHEST CAVITY. HE'LL
NEED BILATERAL TUBES.

07:26.987 --> 07:28.278
BETADINE.

07:28.278 --> 07:30.120
THEN TAKE HIM UP RIGHT NOW
AND START AN EX-LAP.

07:30.120 --> 07:32.242
Richard: PETE, WE'RE GONNA CUT
INTO YOUR CHEST

07:32.242 --> 07:34.454
TO PLACE A TUBE
THAT WILL HELP YOU BREATHE.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.456
EVEN WITH THE PAIN MEDS,
IT'S GONNA HURT LIKE HELL,

07:36.456 --> 07:37.498
BUT IT'S THE ONLY WAY.

07:37.498 --> 07:38.919
ALL RIGHT,
C-SPINE'S CLEAR.

07:38.919 --> 07:40.841
I'LL GET
OUT OF YOUR WAY.

07:40.841 --> 07:42.422
OH, WHOA.

07:42.422 --> 07:44.084
UH, HEY, YOU'RE BLEEDING
QUITE A BIT THERE.

07:44.084 --> 07:46.136
I'M FINE.

07:47.007 --> 07:48.428
NO, YOU GOT SHOT
IN THE LEG.

07:48.428 --> 07:50.140
COME ON.
LET'S GET YOU INTO A BED.

07:50.140 --> 07:51.091
I NEED A NURSE IN HERE.

07:51.091 --> 07:53.764
I'M RIGHT OUTSIDE, PETE,
ALL RIGHT?
MM.

07:53.764 --> 07:55.856
DR. HUNT,
THE OFFICER'S MOTHER IS HERE.

07:55.856 --> 07:57.097
RICHARD, CAN YOU?
YEAH, GO AHEAD.

07:57.097 --> 07:59.099
WE GOT IT.

07:59.099 --> 08:00.521
PETE, YOU READY?

08:04.104 --> 08:07.107
AAAAAAH!

08:07.107 --> 08:08.609
[ SIGHS ]

08:08.609 --> 08:10.320
THEY SAID
I SHOULD SPEAK TO A DOCTOR.

08:10.320 --> 08:12.913
MRS. GIBSON, YOUR SON SUSTAINED
MULTIPLE GUNSHOT WOUNDS.

08:12.913 --> 08:14.414
WE'RE ASSESSING
HIS INJURIES NOW,

08:14.414 --> 08:15.746
AND I WILL UPDATE YOU
AS SOON AS WE KNOW MORE.

08:15.746 --> 08:16.747
WHICH ONE?

08:16.747 --> 08:19.119
I'M SORRY?

08:19.119 --> 08:20.921
WHICH ONE OF MY SONS?
THEY'RE BOTH HERE.

08:22.753 --> 08:26.216
THE GSW TO THE NECK
DEFINITELY HIT THE TRACHEA.

08:26.216 --> 08:28.799
AND HE'S GOT ONE
TO THE ABDOMEN.

08:28.799 --> 08:29.840
[ COUGHS ]
OH.

08:29.840 --> 08:31.592
BRETT, DO NOT TRY TO TALK.
WE GOT YOU.

08:31.592 --> 08:33.263
I NEED TO CRIKE HIM
BEFORE HE LOSES HIS AIRWAY.

08:33.263 --> 08:34.555
OKAY, DO IT QUICKLY.

08:34.555 --> 08:35.976
I GOT TO GET HIM UPSTAIRS

08:35.976 --> 08:37.477
AND EXAMINE
THESE ABDOMINAL INJURIES.

08:37.477 --> 08:39.269
O.R. TWO IS READY FOR US
WHENEVER HE'S STABLE
ENOUGH TO TRANSPORT.

08:39.269 --> 08:42.102
GUYS, THESE TWO COPS
ARE BROTHERS,

08:42.102 --> 08:44.484
AND PETE'S INJURIES
ARE PRETTY SEVERE.

08:44.484 --> 08:46.647
SO LET'S NOT LET THEIR MOTHER
LOSE TWO SONS IN ONE DAY.

08:51.031 --> 08:52.573
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:52.573 --> 08:55.285
MOVE, PLEASE!
MAKE WAY, GUYS.
DOCTOR COMING THROUGH.

08:55.285 --> 08:58.038
EXCUSE ME. EXCUSE ME!
EXCUSE ME, GUYS.

08:58.038 --> 08:59.620
MOVE, PLEASE.

08:59.620 --> 09:02.753
UM, DO YOU THINK
YOU COULD [CLEARS THROAT]

09:02.753 --> 09:04.795
MAYBE RELOCATE
YOUR GUYS?

09:04.795 --> 09:07.127
I COULD TRY,
BUT THEY'LL NEVER LISTEN.

09:07.127 --> 09:08.128
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

09:08.128 --> 09:09.840
IS THERE ANY UPDATE
ON BRETT?

09:09.840 --> 09:14.054
UM, IT IS TOO EARLY TO SAY,
BUT HE'S IN GOOD HANDS.

09:14.054 --> 09:16.346
ALL RIGHT, NOW THIS LOOKS LIKE
A THROUGH-AND-THROUGH.

09:16.346 --> 09:17.347
WHOA.

09:17.347 --> 09:18.769
YOU'RE MISSING
A CHUNK OF MUSCLE,

09:18.769 --> 09:20.020
AND YOU HAVE
EXPOSED BONE FRAGMENTS.

09:20.020 --> 09:21.311
WOW.
WHAT?

09:21.311 --> 09:24.354
UH, NO, I'M -- JUST CAN'T
BELIEVE WHAT I'M LOOKING AT.

09:24.354 --> 09:25.606
THAT BAD, HUH?

09:25.606 --> 09:27.147
NO, NO, NO.
I JUST MEAN I CAN'T BELIEVE

09:27.147 --> 09:29.069
THAT YOU CARRIED YOUR GUY IN
ON THIS LEG.

09:29.069 --> 09:30.320
I DIDN'T HAVE A CHOICE.

09:30.320 --> 09:31.862
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:31.862 --> 09:35.035
NO, OF COURSE YOU DIDN'T.
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

09:35.035 --> 09:36.116
YOU --
YOU CAN TELL YOUR GUYS

09:36.116 --> 09:37.618
THEY CAN BE
WHEREVER THEY NEED TO.

09:37.618 --> 09:40.580
[ SIREN WAILS ]

09:40.580 --> 09:43.123
I'M DAN. PRUITT.

09:43.123 --> 09:45.666
DR. CALLIE TORRES.

09:45.666 --> 09:47.417
[ DOOR OPENS ]
Man: THERE HE IS!

09:47.417 --> 09:49.840
COMING THROUGH!

09:49.840 --> 09:52.212
IS THAT
ANOTHER GUNSHOT VICTIM?

09:52.212 --> 09:53.553
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY.
NO, NO, NO -- EASY.

09:53.553 --> 09:55.806
YOU GOT
TO STAY OFF THIS LEG.

09:55.806 --> 09:57.808
MULTIPLE GSWs
TO THE RIGHT ABDOMEN AND CHEST.

09:57.808 --> 09:58.979
OKAY, TRAUMA THREE.

09:58.979 --> 10:01.101
GET HIM INTUBATED,
PUT IN A CENTRAL LINE,

10:01.101 --> 10:03.063
AND SEND A TRAUMA PANEL.
MOVE!

10:03.063 --> 10:05.025
IS HE ALIVE?
HE'S ALIVE, RIGHT?

10:05.025 --> 10:06.146
DO YOU KNOW HIM?

10:06.146 --> 10:07.898
HE'S ONE
OF THE SUSPECTS.

10:07.898 --> 10:10.991
HE WAS SITTING IN THE CAR WHILE
THE OTHERS WERE IN THE BANK.

10:10.991 --> 10:12.653
I WANT TO KNOW
HOW HE TURNS OUT.

10:14.945 --> 10:16.907
HEY, GUYS, DO YOU SEE
THAT ONE IN THE BACK?

10:16.907 --> 10:18.038
YEAH,
THAT'S ONE OF MINE.

10:18.038 --> 10:20.791
I OPERATED ON HIM
BEFORE HE WAS EVEN BORN.

10:20.791 --> 10:23.623
NOW HE'S TWO HOURS OLD
AND CUTE AS A BUTTON.

10:23.623 --> 10:25.005
A HEALTHY
LITTLE POP-TART.

10:25.005 --> 10:26.006
MM.
POP-TART?

10:26.006 --> 10:27.207
YEAH,
A FETUS THAT'S POPPED.

10:27.207 --> 10:29.049
A BABY THAT'S BORN
FROM HIS MOTHER'S WOMB.

10:29.049 --> 10:30.881
YOU JUST RUINED
POP-TARTS FOR ME.

10:30.881 --> 10:31.882
[ SCOFFS ] YES?

10:31.882 --> 10:33.213
WHAT'S A WOMB?

10:33.213 --> 10:34.424
OH, BOY.

10:34.424 --> 10:35.966
[ BABIES COOING ]

10:35.966 --> 10:38.018
UM...

10:38.018 --> 10:40.891
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:40.891 --> 10:42.432
YOU'RE TANKING AT THIS.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHY

10:42.432 --> 10:44.024
'CAUSE I'M USUALLY
REALLY GOOD WITH KIDS.

10:44.024 --> 10:46.066
I HAVE A QUESTION.
GO AHEAD.

10:46.066 --> 10:47.978
IS THAT POLICEMAN
GOING TO DIE?

10:47.978 --> 10:49.229
HE WAS SHOT
IN THE THROAT.

10:49.229 --> 10:51.361
THAT'S WHY HE WAS
GURGLING BLOOD LIKE THAT.

10:51.361 --> 10:53.573
AND THAT MEANS
HE CAN'T BREATHE,

10:53.573 --> 10:54.945
SO ISN'T HE GOING TO DIE?

10:56.697 --> 10:57.828
HOW WE DOING, PETE?

10:57.828 --> 11:00.490
[ Weakly ]
THINKING OF GOING FOR A RUN.

11:00.490 --> 11:02.662
[ CHUCKLES ] THIS ONE --
ALWAYS THE WISE GUY.

11:02.662 --> 11:03.784
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:03.784 --> 11:05.665
DOES THIS REMIND YOU
OF THAT TRIP TO THE E.R.

11:05.665 --> 11:07.087
WHEN I GOT HIT BY A PITCH?

11:07.087 --> 11:08.668
YOU DIDN'T EVEN TRY
TO GET OUT OF THE WAY.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.050
NOTHING CHANGES, RIGHT?

11:10.050 --> 11:12.963
I GOT TO LEARN TO DUCK.

11:16.386 --> 11:17.637
MOM?

11:17.637 --> 11:19.179
YES?

11:20.891 --> 11:23.183
REMEMBER THAT POTLUCK WE DID
A COUPLE YEARS AGO?

11:23.183 --> 11:25.065
WITH ALL THE GUYS
IN YOUR BACKYARD?

11:25.065 --> 11:26.767
MM-HMM.

11:26.767 --> 11:29.149
WHEN WE GET OUT OF HERE,
WE GOT TO DO THAT AGAIN, OKAY?

11:29.149 --> 11:33.023
BUT BIGGER,
M-MORE PEOPLE.

11:33.023 --> 11:35.025
WE'LL INVITE THESE DOCTORS.
EVERYBODY LOVED IT.

11:35.025 --> 11:37.868
OKAY. SURE, HONEY.

11:37.868 --> 11:40.030
WE WERE GONNA MAKE IT
AN ANNUAL THING, REMEMBER?

11:40.030 --> 11:42.953
MM-HMM.
WE NEVER DID.

11:42.953 --> 11:44.584
WE GOT TO DO THAT --

11:44.584 --> 11:45.786
PETE?

11:45.786 --> 11:46.997
[ COUGHS ]

11:46.997 --> 11:48.128
PETER?!
[ MONITOR BEEPS RAPIDLY ]

11:50.210 --> 11:52.212
WE'RE GONNA TAKE GOOD CARE
OF YOUR BOY, MA'AM.

11:52.212 --> 11:53.673
WE NEED PIERCE
BACK IN HERE!

11:55.295 --> 11:58.929
THEY'VE GOT HIM, MRS. GIBSON.
PETE'S A TOUGH KID.

12:02.222 --> 12:04.514
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

12:04.514 --> 12:06.186
THERE'S A TRAUMA.
I DIDN'T PAGE YOU.

12:06.186 --> 12:08.148
AMELIA, I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.
LET ME HELP.

12:08.148 --> 12:09.729
YOU'RE THE BOSS.
I'LL DO WHATEVER YOU NEED.

12:09.729 --> 12:12.112
YOU WANT TO HELP?
TAKE MY ANEURYSM.

12:12.112 --> 12:14.354
O.R. FOUR -- GO CLIP IT.

12:14.354 --> 12:17.067
AND THERE IT IS.
THAT PAUSE.

12:17.067 --> 12:19.319
THE ONE THAT MEANS, "I DON'T
WANT THE BORING ANEURYSM,

12:19.319 --> 12:21.451
I WANT THE BIG,
EXCITING NEURO TRAUMA."

12:21.451 --> 12:23.123
YOU DON'T DO SECOND PLACE.

12:23.123 --> 12:25.245
I DO NOW.
I'M CLIPPING AN ANEURYSM.

12:26.576 --> 12:28.168
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

12:28.168 --> 12:29.749
WE HAVE AN AUDIENCE
OUT THERE.

12:29.749 --> 12:32.582
I KNOW.
STARTING CARDIAC MASSAGE.

12:32.582 --> 12:35.255
HANG ANOTHER UNIT OF BLOOD
ON THE RAPID INFUSER.

12:35.255 --> 12:36.546
Nurse: RIGHT AWAY.

12:36.546 --> 12:38.298
COME ON.

12:38.298 --> 12:41.141
COME ON, PETE.
GIVE ME SOMETHING.

12:41.141 --> 12:43.473
GIVE ME ANYTHING.

12:46.056 --> 12:47.978
I HAVE A HEARTBEAT.

12:47.978 --> 12:49.689
[ MONITOR BEEPS STEADILY ]

12:49.689 --> 12:51.231
GOT A PULSE.
THERE HE IS.

12:52.192 --> 12:53.944
WHAT'S THE STORY?
Owen: TRAUMATIC ARREST.

12:53.944 --> 12:55.105
DOWN FOR 14 MINUTES.

13:00.320 --> 13:01.952
PUPILS ARE FIXED.

13:01.952 --> 13:03.533
NO.

13:03.533 --> 13:05.205
WE LOST HIM?

13:05.205 --> 13:06.246
NO CORNEAL REFLEX,
EITHER.

13:06.246 --> 13:07.998
I'LL DO A FORMAL EXAM
IN SIX HOURS,

13:07.998 --> 13:09.669
BUT SOMEONE NEEDS
TO PREPARE THE FAMILY.

13:11.621 --> 13:13.914
HE'S MOST LIKELY
BRAIN DEAD.

13:13.914 --> 13:15.175
I'M SORRY.

13:16.716 --> 13:18.048
WE LOST HIM.

13:18.048 --> 13:21.091
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

13:33.563 --> 13:35.195
PETE'S BODY
IS STILL STRONG,

13:35.195 --> 13:38.108
BUT I'M AFRAID
HIS BRAIN

13:38.108 --> 13:41.201
HAS BEEN DEPRIVED OF OXYGEN
FOR TOO LONG.

13:42.943 --> 13:44.945
[ Voice breaking ]
HE WON'T WAKE UP?

13:44.945 --> 13:46.536
NO.

13:46.536 --> 13:48.999
I'M AFRAID
HE'S BRAIN DEAD.

13:51.081 --> 13:52.622
[ SIGHS ]

13:52.622 --> 13:55.956
MRS. GIBSON,
I AM SO SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

13:55.956 --> 13:57.257
AND BRETT?

13:57.257 --> 13:59.219
HE'S STILL IN SURGERY.

13:59.219 --> 14:01.301
AND HE'S GONNA BE OKAY?

14:01.301 --> 14:03.053
HE'S STABLE NOW.

14:03.053 --> 14:05.805
WE'RE TAKING CARE OF HIM
AS BEST WE CAN.

14:08.268 --> 14:11.431
WHO WOULD DO THIS
TO THEM?

14:11.431 --> 14:14.104
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY, BLOOD IN THE ABDOMEN.

14:14.104 --> 14:15.105
POSSIBLE LIVER INJURY.

14:15.105 --> 14:18.858
TURN HIM ON THREE.
ONE, TWO, THREE.

14:18.858 --> 14:20.440
NO VISIBLE WOUNDS
ON HIS BACK.

14:20.440 --> 14:22.652
LOOKS LIKE A BULLET'S
LODGED NEAR HIS SPINE.

14:22.652 --> 14:24.824
PAGE NEURO!
TELL THEM TO MEET US IN THE O.R.

14:24.824 --> 14:27.287
BAILEY, THERE'S A COP
ASKING ABOUT THIS --

14:27.287 --> 14:29.119
OH, MY GOD,
HOW OLD IS HE, 15?

14:29.119 --> 14:30.951
TOO YOUNG
TO BE PLAYING WITH GUNS.

14:30.951 --> 14:32.292
THIS KID WAS REALLY
SHOOTING AT COPS?

14:32.292 --> 14:34.124
BUT HE'S THE DRIVER,
ACCORDING TO THE POLICE.

14:34.124 --> 14:35.205
ALLEGED DRIVER.

14:36.086 --> 14:37.047
CAN I TELL HIM ANYTHING?

14:37.047 --> 14:39.549
TELL HIM HE'S STILL ALIVE,
FOR NOW.

14:39.549 --> 14:41.962
NOTIFY O.R. SIX WE'RE ON OUR WAY
UP WITH AN EMERGENCY EX-LAP.

14:41.962 --> 14:43.053
Nurse: RIGHT AWAY.

14:43.053 --> 14:46.096
WHOA!
WHOA!
WHOA!

14:46.096 --> 14:47.137
AWESOME!

14:47.137 --> 14:48.308
WHOA.
WHOA.
WHOA.

14:48.308 --> 14:51.061
WHAT DID I TELL YOU?
PRETTY COOL, RIGHT?

14:51.061 --> 14:52.142
QUESTIONS?

14:52.142 --> 14:53.353
ME! ME! ME!
I DO!

14:53.353 --> 14:54.474
MM...

14:54.474 --> 14:57.187
I GOT A MARBLE STUCK
IN MY NOSE ONCE.

14:58.068 --> 14:59.980
Alex: THAT'S...
NOT A QUESTION.

14:59.980 --> 15:01.021
GROSS.

15:01.021 --> 15:02.572
ARE YOU SURE
THIS IS OKAY?

15:02.572 --> 15:04.154
YEAH,
IT'S TOTALLY FINE.

15:04.154 --> 15:05.155
WE GOT THE NAIL OUT.

15:05.155 --> 15:06.156
"WE"?

15:06.156 --> 15:07.907
YOU PULLED THAT NAIL
OUT OF A GUY'S HEAD?

15:07.907 --> 15:08.949
I DID.

15:08.949 --> 15:10.790
WOW.

15:10.790 --> 15:11.992
SO, YOU'RE KIND OF
A BADASS, HUH?

15:11.992 --> 15:14.334
I AM.

15:14.334 --> 15:15.745
Alex:
OKAY, NEXT SLIDE.

15:15.745 --> 15:17.537
AND THIS IS A COFFEE CAN
IN A MAN'S ABDOMEN.

15:17.537 --> 15:19.209
COOL!
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

15:19.209 --> 15:20.670
OKAY,
NOW THAT IS...

15:20.670 --> 15:21.711
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:21.711 --> 15:23.423
THAT'S DEFINITELY
NOT APPROPRIATE.

15:23.423 --> 15:25.255
[ LAUGHS ]

15:25.255 --> 15:27.717
IT'S TOTALLY FINE.
WE GOT THE CAN OUT, TOO.

15:27.717 --> 15:28.758
S-SURE, YEAH.

15:28.758 --> 15:30.720
BUT THEY'RE GONNA ASK
HOW IT GOT IN THERE.

15:30.720 --> 15:32.222
[ LAUGHS ]

15:32.222 --> 15:34.644
OKAY, GUYS, BUS IS HERE.
LET'S ROLL OUT.

15:34.644 --> 15:36.936
[ CHILDREN GROAN ]
WHAT IS THAT?

15:36.936 --> 15:38.058
IT'S A COFFEE CAN.

15:40.690 --> 15:42.562
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO, GUYS.
COME ON.

15:42.562 --> 15:45.565
DANG, JUST WHEN WE WERE
STARTING TO HAVE FUN.

15:45.565 --> 15:47.827
BYE!
BYE.

15:50.991 --> 15:53.333
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
HEY.

15:53.333 --> 15:55.205
HEY.
I THOUGHT AMEL--

15:55.205 --> 15:58.078
UH, I WAS LOOKING
FOR THE OTHER DR. SHEPHERD.

15:58.078 --> 15:59.629
SHE'S BUSY
WITH THE TRAUMA.
AH.

15:59.629 --> 16:01.131
DID YOU TALK TO HER?

16:01.131 --> 16:02.422
I DID.
AND?

16:02.422 --> 16:04.504
I'M CLIPPING AN ANEURYSM
FOR HER.

16:04.504 --> 16:06.886
HUH.
AND YOU'RE GOOD WITH THAT?

16:06.886 --> 16:08.138
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

16:08.138 --> 16:09.299
WELL, IT'S A FAR CRY

16:09.299 --> 16:11.721
FROM MAPPING THE BRAIN
FOR THE PRESIDENT.

16:11.721 --> 16:12.722
SHE'S BEEN TALKING
TO YOU.

16:12.722 --> 16:14.594
A BIT.

16:14.594 --> 16:17.437
I'M GOOD WITH IT.
ACTUALLY, I'M A LITTLE NERVOUS.

16:17.437 --> 16:19.149
YOU SURE YOU WANT
TO TELL ME THAT?

16:19.149 --> 16:21.731
NO, I MEAN, IT'S A GOOD NERVOUS,
UH, GOOD, EXCITED.

16:21.731 --> 16:23.063
I JUST HAVEN'T OPERATED
IN MONTHS, AND...

16:23.063 --> 16:25.025
[ SIGHS ]

16:25.025 --> 16:26.986
IT FEELS REALLY GOOD
TO BE BACK.

16:26.986 --> 16:29.109
WELL, WE'RE GLAD
TO HAVE YOU BACK.

16:29.109 --> 16:31.821
HEY, HUNT.
WE SHOULD HANG OUT MORE.

16:31.821 --> 16:32.912
DO YOU FISH?

16:32.912 --> 16:34.244
NEVER. NEVER HAVE.

16:34.244 --> 16:35.825
YOU SHOULD.
WE WILL.

16:35.825 --> 16:36.876
OKAY.

16:36.876 --> 16:38.828
[ LAUGHS ] ALL RIGHT.
OKAY.

16:38.828 --> 16:42.252
THE BULLET'S NICKED THE BONE,
BUT THERE'S NO CORD DAMAGE.

16:42.252 --> 16:44.214
I'D SAY LEAVE IT.
YOUR CALL.

16:44.214 --> 16:47.047
MM, THIS LIVER'S IN BAD SHAPE.
IT'S ACTUALLY AVULSED.

16:47.047 --> 16:49.089
THE BLOOD SUPPLY'S
COMPLETELY GONE.

16:49.089 --> 16:51.131
A KID THIS YOUNG
HELPS COMMIT ROBBERY?

16:51.131 --> 16:53.012
[ SIGHS ]
HE'S NOT MUCH OLDER THAN TUCK.

16:54.474 --> 16:56.476
AW, DAMN IT.

16:56.476 --> 16:58.638
NO, THERE'S NO SAVING
THIS LIVER.

16:58.638 --> 17:01.191
HE'S GONNA NEED A TRANSPLANT
AND FAST.

17:01.191 --> 17:02.522
WOW.

17:02.522 --> 17:05.195
SO, SOMEONE DOESN'T GET A LIVER
BECAUSE THIS SHOOTER GETS ONE?

17:05.195 --> 17:07.907
HE WON'T SURVIVE
WITHOUT ONE.

17:07.907 --> 17:09.569
AND WE DON'T KNOW IF THIS BOY
EVEN HAD A GUN ON HIM.

17:09.569 --> 17:11.151
PLEASE.

17:11.151 --> 17:13.073
IF HE DIDN'T SHOOT A COP, HE WAS
AN ACCESSORY TO SOMEONE WHO DID.

17:13.073 --> 17:14.284
HE'LL BE TRIED
AS AN ADULT.

17:14.284 --> 17:15.825
HEY, HE'S A PATIENT.

17:15.825 --> 17:17.867
WE DON'T PAY ATTENTION
TO THE BACKSTORY.

17:17.867 --> 17:19.249
WE DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT HIM.

17:19.249 --> 17:20.580
WE KNOW
WE LOST A COP TODAY.

17:20.580 --> 17:21.921
AND WE KNOW HE CHOSE

17:21.921 --> 17:23.963
TO HELP HIS FRIENDS
HOLD PEOPLE UP AT GUNPOINT.

17:23.963 --> 17:26.966
YOU DO THAT, YOU PRETTY MUCH
GET THE HAND YOU'RE DEALT.

17:26.966 --> 17:28.168
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:28.168 --> 17:31.221
PACK HIM
AND AGGRESSIVELY RESUSCITATE.

17:31.221 --> 17:33.173
THEN LEAVE HIM HERE
WITH A SCRUB NURSE.

17:33.173 --> 17:35.385
AND YOU GO FIND HIS FAMILY.
I'LL CALL UNOS.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.808
ALL RIGHT. [ SIGHS ]

17:38.808 --> 17:40.100
FIRST THINGS FIRST.

17:40.100 --> 17:41.641
I CHECKED ON YOUR PARTNER,
BRETT.

17:41.641 --> 17:42.682
HE'S STILL IN SURGERY.

17:42.682 --> 17:43.893
MINIMAL INTERNAL INJURY.

17:43.893 --> 17:45.775
THEY'RE STILL WORKING ON
THE TRACHEA REPAIR,

17:45.775 --> 17:47.987
BUT IT DIDN'T HIT
ANY OF THE MAJOR BLOOD VESSELS,

17:47.987 --> 17:49.149
WHICH IS
REALLY GREAT NEWS.

17:49.149 --> 17:50.150
THANK YOU.

17:50.150 --> 17:52.152
THAT'S...THANKS.

17:52.152 --> 17:53.613
NOW YOU.

17:53.613 --> 17:56.536
YOU AREN'T GOING TO NEED
SURGERY, JUST A SPLINT,

17:56.536 --> 17:58.328
BUT IT DOES MEAN THAT
YOU'LL NEED TO STAY OFF OF IT

17:58.328 --> 17:59.909
FOR AT LEAST SIX WEEKS,
MAYBE EIGHT.

17:59.909 --> 18:03.082
YOU THINK THAT MEANS ONE WEEK,
I CAN TELL.

18:03.082 --> 18:05.044
BUT IT MEANS SIX.
AT LEAST, OKAY?

18:05.044 --> 18:09.129
AFTER TODAY, YOU KNOW,

18:09.129 --> 18:11.591
I THINK I MIGHT WANT
TO RIDE A DESK FOR A WHILE.

18:11.591 --> 18:14.053
AFTER 14 YEARS ON THE FORCE,
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME

18:14.053 --> 18:15.845
I EVER HAD TO FIRE MY WEAPON
ON DUTY.

18:15.845 --> 18:17.387
FIRST TIME
WE WERE EVER FIRED AT.

18:17.387 --> 18:20.980
[ SIGHS ] WOW.

18:20.980 --> 18:22.812
WELL, IT SOUNDS LIKE
IT WAS A GOOD RUN.

18:22.812 --> 18:24.144
I'M SORRY IT ENDED.

18:24.144 --> 18:25.225
THANK YOU.

18:25.225 --> 18:27.397
ANY WORD ON THE KID?

18:27.397 --> 18:29.569
UH, NO.
STILL IN THE O.R.

18:29.569 --> 18:30.780
OKAY.

18:30.780 --> 18:33.153
I JUST NEED SOMETHING GOOD
TO COME OUT OF THIS DAY.

18:35.114 --> 18:37.497
Meredith: ABDOMINAL INJURIES
ARE UNDER CONTROL.

18:37.497 --> 18:39.659
I'M READY TO CLOSE.
YOU ABOUT DONE, KEPNER?

18:39.659 --> 18:41.411
ALMOST.
THEN I'LL LET WILSON CLOSE.

18:41.411 --> 18:42.872
THANK YOU, DR. KEPNER.

18:42.872 --> 18:46.085
OKAY, UPDATE ME
WHEN YOU'RE DONE.

18:46.085 --> 18:47.587
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
HE'S DE-SATTING.

18:47.587 --> 18:49.629
WHAT IS IT?

18:49.629 --> 18:50.750
UH, IT'S NOT ME.

18:50.750 --> 18:52.752
FIELD IS CLEAR.
THERE'S NO BLEEDERS.

18:52.752 --> 18:56.716
NOTHING HERE.
TUBE'S INTACT. NO LEAKS.

18:57.387 --> 18:58.928
CHECK HIS PUPILS.

19:04.684 --> 19:06.105
NO RESPONSE.

19:06.105 --> 19:08.188
OH, DAMN IT.
DAMN IT, DAMN IT, BRETT.

19:08.188 --> 19:09.229
DID HE THROW A CLOT?

19:09.229 --> 19:11.821
WE WON'T KNOW
UNTIL WE GET HIM UP TO C.T.

19:11.821 --> 19:13.983
PAGE NEURO,
ASK THEM TO MEET US POST-OP.

19:13.983 --> 19:15.905
RIGHT AWAY.
WE HAD HIM.

19:15.905 --> 19:17.777
WE HAD HIM.

19:25.044 --> 19:27.547
I'M SO SORRY,
MRS. GIBSON.

19:27.547 --> 19:29.549
BRETT'S GONE.

19:29.549 --> 19:32.382
[ GASPS ]

19:32.382 --> 19:35.255
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

19:35.255 --> 19:38.678
I KNEW THIS COULD HAPPEN.

19:38.678 --> 19:41.060
[ SIGHS ]

19:43.853 --> 19:49.188
I'M AFRAID BRETT SUFFERED
A LARGE STROKE DURING SURGERY.

19:49.188 --> 19:51.861
UNFORTUNATELY,
IT'S NOT UNCOMMON.

19:51.861 --> 19:54.864
IN THIS CASE,
THE DAMAGE WAS VERY SEVERE,

19:54.864 --> 19:57.026
AND IT RESULTED
IN BRAIN DEATH.

19:57.026 --> 20:00.079
MRS. GIBSON, THERE WAS NOTHING
ANYONE COULD DO.

20:00.079 --> 20:04.244
BUT HIS HAND
IS STILL WARM IN MINE.

20:04.244 --> 20:08.037
HIS HEART'S BEATING.
I CAN SEE HIS BREATH.

20:08.037 --> 20:11.040
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:11.040 --> 20:14.964
I WOKE UP THIS MORNING THE
MOTHER OF TWO PERFECT CHILDREN.

20:14.964 --> 20:17.547
HAPPY, PROUD.

20:17.547 --> 20:19.218
AND NOW...

20:19.218 --> 20:21.100
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:21.100 --> 20:24.264
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND.

20:24.264 --> 20:27.477
VERY SORRY, MRS. GIBSON.

20:27.477 --> 20:30.520
OH, GOD.

20:30.520 --> 20:32.772
[ SOBBING ]

20:40.950 --> 20:42.362
[ SUCTIONING ]

20:42.362 --> 20:43.783
HEY,
HOW'S HE DOING?

20:43.783 --> 20:46.536
PRESSURE'S DROPPING,
AND HE'S OOZING FROM HIS DRAINS.

20:46.536 --> 20:49.329
WELL, UNOS DIDN'T HAVE
ANYTHING AVAILABLE.

20:49.329 --> 20:53.042
NEITHER DID ANY OF THE HOSPITALS
HERE OR IN OREGON.

20:53.042 --> 20:54.253
DID YOU TRACK DOWN
HIS FAMILY?

20:54.253 --> 20:55.545
OH, HE'S IN THE SYSTEM.

20:55.545 --> 20:57.967
HIS LATEST FOSTER PARENTS
HAVEN'T SEEN HIM

20:57.967 --> 20:59.799
SINCE THE NIGHT HE CAME
TO STAY WITH THEM, THOUGH,

20:59.799 --> 21:01.551
SO, UH, THEY'RE NOT EXACTLY
RACING DOWN HERE.

21:01.551 --> 21:02.682
SO HE'S ALONE?

21:02.682 --> 21:05.144
AND HE'S JUST
GONNA DIE HERE, ALONE.

21:05.144 --> 21:06.596
HOW MUCH TIME
DO WE HAVE?

21:06.596 --> 21:08.227
WELL, WITHOUT A LIVER,
HE'S GOT...

21:08.227 --> 21:09.228
HOURS.

21:12.061 --> 21:15.194
BEN, STAY WITH HIM.
KEEP HIS SBP ABOVE 100.

21:15.194 --> 21:16.986
WHERE YOU GOING?

21:16.986 --> 21:19.108
WELL, I-I-I JUST CAN'T
GO TO SLEEP TONIGHT

21:19.108 --> 21:22.161
KNOWING I DIDN'T TRY
ABSOLUTELY EVERYTHING.

21:22.161 --> 21:23.323
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:23.323 --> 21:25.405
GOD, I MEAN,
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

21:25.405 --> 21:27.286
THIS DAY STARTED OUT
SO GREAT.

21:27.286 --> 21:29.078
"BLESSED,"
I THINK YOU SAID.

21:29.078 --> 21:31.501
NOW I HAVE TO GO ASK THE MOM
FOR HER SON'S ORGANS.

21:31.501 --> 21:32.752
THAT SUCKS.

21:32.752 --> 21:34.173
IS THIS HOW IT HAS TO BE?

21:34.173 --> 21:36.125
IF I'M THAT HAPPY, SOMEONE ELSE
HAS TO BE THAT UNHAPPY?

21:36.125 --> 21:40.009
I MEAN, THIS POOR COPS' MOM
LOST TWO SONS TODAY.

21:40.009 --> 21:42.592
WHAT? TWO SONS?

21:42.592 --> 21:44.844
Maggie: STROKE.

21:44.844 --> 21:45.975
ON THE TABLE.

21:45.975 --> 21:47.597
OH, GOD.

21:47.597 --> 21:49.228
UH, UGH.

21:49.228 --> 21:51.190
OKAY, YOU HAVE TO TELL
THEIR COMMANDING OFFICER.

21:51.190 --> 21:53.192
HE'S BEEN ASKING
FOR GOOD NEWS ALL DAY.

21:53.192 --> 21:55.024
Meredith:
SURE, I'LL GO TALK TO HIM

21:55.024 --> 21:56.816
AS SOON AS I'M DONE
ASKING THE MOM

21:56.816 --> 21:58.988
IF WE CAN CUT UP HER HERO SONS
FOR BODY PARTS.

21:58.988 --> 22:01.070
WHICH, WHAT TIME IS IT?

22:01.070 --> 22:02.742
THOSE ORGANS
WILL BE DEAD SOON, TOO.

22:02.742 --> 22:04.654
ALSO, THE COMMANDING OFFICER
KEEPS ASKING

22:04.654 --> 22:06.035
ABOUT THE KID
THEY BROUGHT IN.

22:06.035 --> 22:07.447
I THINK IT'S 'CAUSE HE JUST
WANTS TO HEAR THAT HE'S DEAD.

22:07.447 --> 22:08.708
CAN YOU BLAME HIM?

22:08.708 --> 22:10.249
UH...

22:10.249 --> 22:12.121
I SHOWED
A BUNCH OF SCHOOL KIDS

22:12.121 --> 22:14.664
THAT X-RAY OF A COFFEE CAN
STUCK UP SOME GUY'S BUTT.

22:14.664 --> 22:16.005
RIVETING.
ALEX.

22:16.005 --> 22:17.377
READ THE ROOM, MAN.

22:17.377 --> 22:19.338
I WAS JUST TRYING
TO CHEER YOU UP.

22:19.338 --> 22:21.921
OH, GREY, UM, IS YOUR PATIENT
AN ORGAN DONOR?

22:21.921 --> 22:24.924
I'M ABOUT
TO GO ASK HER NOW.

22:24.924 --> 22:26.926
OH, WHEN? NOW?
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,
THERE'S A WINDOW.

22:26.926 --> 22:28.227
I KNOW, BAILEY.
I KNOW.

22:28.227 --> 22:30.179
AND I HAVE A 15-YEAR-OLD BOY
OPEN IN THE O.R.

22:30.179 --> 22:32.432
WHO NEEDS A LIVER,
AND UNOS IS COMING UP EMPTY.

22:32.432 --> 22:35.024
15-YEAR-OLD?
YOU'RE NOT TALKING ABOUT --

22:35.024 --> 22:37.437
I CHECKED YOUR PATIENT,
AND HE'S A PERFECT MATCH.

22:37.437 --> 22:39.148
AND WE CAN DO IT TODAY

22:39.148 --> 22:42.111
IF THE MOTHER WOULD CONSIDER
A DIRECTED DONATION.

22:42.111 --> 22:43.443
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

22:43.443 --> 22:46.746
OKAY, ALL I'M ASKING IS
THAT YOU BRING IT UP WITH HER.

22:46.746 --> 22:48.037
JUST ASK.
NO!

22:48.037 --> 22:50.700
HE WILL NOT SURVIVE
WITHOUT A NEW LIVER.

22:50.700 --> 22:53.583
BAILEY, ASKING FOR
HER SONS' ORGANS IS HARD ENOUGH.

22:53.583 --> 22:55.875
NOW YOU WANT ME TO ASK HER
FOR ORGANS

22:55.875 --> 22:58.047
TO GIVE TO THE KID
THAT KILLED HER SONS?

22:58.047 --> 22:59.549
OKAY,
TAKE AWAY THE STORY.

22:59.549 --> 23:01.761
RIGHT, TAKE AWAY
THE GOOD GUYS AND BAD GUYS.

23:01.761 --> 23:06.005
IT'S A CHILD WHO NEEDS AN ORGAN
AND A PATIENT WITH ONE TO GIVE.

23:06.005 --> 23:09.388
BAILEY, THAT WOMAN
LOST EVERYTHING TODAY.

23:09.388 --> 23:10.389
I KNOW!

23:10.389 --> 23:12.141
OKAY, YOU DON'T THINK
I KNOW THAT?

23:12.141 --> 23:15.224
BUT ETHICALLY, YOU HAVE TO.

23:15.224 --> 23:17.316
ETHICALLY, I'M LOOKING OUT
FOR THE BEST INTEREST

23:17.316 --> 23:19.318
OF MY PATIENT
AND HIS FAMILY.

23:22.442 --> 23:24.073
HEY, THANKS
FOR WALKING US OUT.

23:24.073 --> 23:25.695
YOU KNOW,
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

23:25.695 --> 23:27.657
WITH YOUR SENSE OF DIRECTION,
I KIND OF DID.

23:27.657 --> 23:29.408
THAT'S...

23:29.408 --> 23:31.200
THAT IS ABSOLUTELY TRUE.

23:31.200 --> 23:32.872
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:32.872 --> 23:35.495
I KNOW IT'S BEEN A DRAG FOR YOU,
BUT I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

23:35.495 --> 23:38.588
YOU REALLY DID MAKE IT FUN,
SO THANK YOU.

23:38.588 --> 23:39.589
WELL, THANK YOU.

23:39.589 --> 23:40.670
WHERE'S JULIE?
YEAH, SO --

23:40.670 --> 23:42.592
WHAT?
I CAN'T FIND JULIE.

23:42.592 --> 23:43.673
SHE'S NOT ON THE BUS.
HAVE YOU SEEN HER?

23:43.673 --> 23:44.804
NO.

23:44.804 --> 23:46.716
OH.
WAIT,
JULIE IS THE ONE WHO --

23:46.716 --> 23:48.217
WHO WAS ASKING
ABOUT THE POLICEMAN.

23:48.217 --> 23:49.218
THAT JULIE.

23:49.218 --> 23:51.140
SHE WAS JUST RIGHT HERE,
WASN'T SHE?

23:51.140 --> 23:52.181
JULIE?

23:52.181 --> 23:53.763
HEY, DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL FIND HER.

23:53.763 --> 23:55.104
WE'LL FIND HER,
MA'AM.

23:55.104 --> 23:57.186
I KNOW
THIS IS A DIFFICULT TIME

23:57.186 --> 24:00.319
AND IT'S THE LAST THING
YOU'D WANT TO THINK ABOUT,

24:00.319 --> 24:03.022
BUT YOU DO HAVE
A DECISION TO MAKE.

24:03.022 --> 24:05.114
DO YOU KNOW IF YOUR SONS

24:05.114 --> 24:08.528
WOULD HAVE CONSIDERED
BECOMING ORGAN DONORS?

24:08.528 --> 24:13.953
THEY WERE ALWAYS HELPING PEOPLE,
EVEN AS LITTLE BOYS.

24:13.953 --> 24:15.915
THAT'S WHY THEY WANTED
TO BE POLICEMEN.

24:15.915 --> 24:17.166
WELL, BRETT DID.

24:17.166 --> 24:19.919
PETE -- HE WAS ALWAYS
A LITTLE MIXED UP.

24:19.919 --> 24:23.543
HE JUST FOLLOWED BRETT,
BUT THEN HE -- HE FOUND HIS WAY.

24:23.543 --> 24:28.387
I THINK THAT...
THAT'S WHAT THEY'D WANT.

24:28.387 --> 24:30.259
I THINK
THEY'D WANT TO HELP.

24:30.259 --> 24:31.300
OKAY.

24:31.300 --> 24:33.352
THERE'LL BE SOME PAPERWORK
TO FILL OUT.

24:33.352 --> 24:34.894
UH, MRS. GIBSON?
SURE.

24:34.894 --> 24:37.647
IT IS POSSIBLE
FOR YOU TO DESIGNATE

24:37.647 --> 24:40.560
WHERE YOU WANT
YOUR SON'S LIVER TO GO.

24:40.560 --> 24:43.402
UH, SPECIFICALLY,
I HAVE A YOUNG PATIENT --

24:43.402 --> 24:46.526
HE'S ONLY 15 --
DESPERATELY IN NEED OF A LIVER.

24:46.526 --> 24:49.238
HE'S A PERFECT MATCH
WITH YOUR SON BRETT.

24:49.238 --> 24:51.160
OH, GOD.

24:51.160 --> 24:53.112
SO YOUNG.
THAT'S TERRIBLE.

24:53.112 --> 24:55.995
AND YOU THINK
BRETT COULD HELP THAT BOY?

24:55.995 --> 24:57.206
HE COULD.

24:57.206 --> 24:58.878
YOU COULD.

24:58.878 --> 25:01.541
15? MM.

25:01.541 --> 25:03.042
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

25:03.042 --> 25:07.547
WELL, HE -- MM, WAS --
WAS INJURED IN THE ROBBERY.

25:07.547 --> 25:09.218
WAIT,
YOU'RE NOT SAYING --

25:09.218 --> 25:11.551
OKAY, MRS. GIBSON,
UH, I-I UNDERSTAND

25:11.551 --> 25:13.843
IT'S AN IMPOSSIBLE QUESTION,

25:13.843 --> 25:15.224
BUT WE NEED TO ASK --

25:15.224 --> 25:18.017
NO, HE --
HE MURDERED MY BOYS.

25:18.017 --> 25:21.520
YOU HAVE THE AUDACITY
TO WALK IN HERE

25:21.520 --> 25:25.024
AND ASK ME
TO GIVE HIM MY CHILD'S BODY,

25:25.024 --> 25:28.197
MY CHILD'S BLOOD,
SO HE CAN LIVE?

25:31.070 --> 25:34.153
NO, HE'S NOT GETTING ANYTHING.
HE CAN GO TO HELL.

25:36.956 --> 25:39.999
GREY, WELL,
I HAD TO TRY FOR MY --

25:39.999 --> 25:41.290
FOR YOUR PATIENT,
I KNOW.
YEAH.

25:41.290 --> 25:43.583
BUT NOW THAT'S DOZENS
OF TRANSPLANT PATIENTS

25:43.583 --> 25:45.544
THAT YOU JUST SCREWED OUT
OF A CHANCE.

25:57.136 --> 25:58.848
WHAT HAPPENED?
MY DAUGHTER'S MISSING.

25:58.848 --> 26:01.060
I KNEW WE SHOULD HAVE
GONE HOME IMMEDIATELY.

26:01.060 --> 26:02.732
MA'AM, JUST TRY
AND STAY CALM, OKAY?

26:02.732 --> 26:04.604
IS SHE THE KIND OF KID
WHO WANDERS OFF?

26:04.604 --> 26:05.685
NO.

26:05.685 --> 26:07.186
NO. WHAT IF
SOMEONE TOOK HER?

26:07.186 --> 26:08.527
DO YOU THINK
SOMEONE TOOK HER?

26:08.527 --> 26:11.150
NOW, LOOK -- WE TOOK
A CLASS PICTURE THIS MORNING.

26:11.150 --> 26:12.151
THIS IS HER.

26:12.151 --> 26:14.033
THIS IS WHAT SHE'S WEARING.

26:14.033 --> 26:15.955
I'LL SEND THIS OUT
TO MY GUYS,

26:15.955 --> 26:17.957
AND WE'LL TRACK HER DOWN,
OKAY?

26:17.957 --> 26:20.199
EDWARDS, HAVE THE PAGING SYSTEM
CALL FOR HER.

26:20.199 --> 26:21.580
YOU KNOW
WHAT THE GIRL LOOKS LIKE.

26:21.580 --> 26:23.202
START CHECKING THE FLOORS,
ROOM BY ROOM.

26:23.202 --> 26:25.004
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
OKAY.

26:25.004 --> 26:27.086
Woman on P.A.:
JULIE HAMILTON, JULIE HAMILTON,

26:27.086 --> 26:28.467
PLEASE REPORT TO...

26:28.467 --> 26:29.919
AND HE'S SO CUTE.

26:29.919 --> 26:31.300
AND HE'S INCREDIBLE
WITH THE KIDS.

26:31.300 --> 26:34.173
REALLY? SEEMS LIKE
HE WOULDN'T HAVE LOST ONE, THEN.

26:34.173 --> 26:35.805
NO, NO,
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN HIM

26:35.805 --> 26:38.217
WHEN SHE ACTUALLY
WENT MISSING -- HE STEPPED UP.

26:38.217 --> 26:40.770
AND -- WELL, HE MIGHT BE
A LITTLE YOUNG FOR ME, THOUGH.

26:40.770 --> 26:42.521
WELL,
BETTER THAN TOO OLD.

26:42.521 --> 26:43.813
[ SIGHS ]

26:43.813 --> 26:45.935
AND CAN I REALLY DATE
A TEACHER?

26:45.935 --> 26:47.316
WHY NOT?

26:47.316 --> 26:49.729
HE GETS OFF WORK AT 3:00 P.M.
I GET OFF WORK AT 3:00 A.M.

26:49.729 --> 26:52.111
WHEN WILL WE HAVE TIME TO --
[ SIGHS ] STEPH, STOP. STOP!

26:52.111 --> 26:54.363
THIS ISN'T SHIRTLESS CAT GUY
ON THE INTERNET.

26:54.363 --> 26:57.156
STOP LOOKING FOR REASONS
NOT TO LIKE THE NICE, CUTE GUY.

26:57.156 --> 26:59.038
YOU'RE HOT FOR TEACHER.
LET IT HAPPEN.

26:59.038 --> 27:02.331
[ SIGHS ]
I'M GONNA LET IT HAPPEN.

27:04.413 --> 27:05.705
IS THERE ANY HOPE?

27:05.705 --> 27:06.916
I'M AFRAID NOT.

27:06.916 --> 27:09.548
WE'LL OBSERVE THEM
FOR THE NEXT SIX HOURS,

27:09.548 --> 27:11.250
BUT THERE'S NO
BRAIN ACTIVITY AT ALL.

27:11.250 --> 27:13.843
HOW'S THEIR MOM?

27:13.843 --> 27:16.175
SHE IS GOING TO NEED ALL
THE SUPPORT YOU CAN GIVE HER.

27:16.175 --> 27:18.888
THANK YOU.

27:18.888 --> 27:20.760
OKAY.

27:20.760 --> 27:22.141
WHAT ABOUT THE KID?

27:22.141 --> 27:23.142
JARED?

27:23.142 --> 27:25.224
Callie: LISTEN, DAN,
I KNOW YOU'RE ANGRY,

27:25.224 --> 27:26.896
AND I KNOW
THAT YOU NEED TO KNOW,

27:26.896 --> 27:28.567
BUT WE CAN'T TALK ABOUT
A SUSPECT'S CONDITION,
NOT LEGALLY.

27:28.567 --> 27:31.861
I'M NOT LOOKING
TO SETTLE A SCORE, OKAY?

27:31.861 --> 27:33.402
I KNEW THIS KID.

27:33.402 --> 27:35.234
BRETT KNEW THIS KID.

27:35.234 --> 27:36.906
WE PUT HIM IN JUVIE.

27:36.906 --> 27:39.538
WE GOT HIM INTO
THE FOSTER SYSTEM.

27:39.538 --> 27:40.700
WE TRIED.

27:42.782 --> 27:44.744
JARED'S ONE OF THOSE KIDS,
YOU KNOW.

27:44.744 --> 27:46.205
HE'S SMART.
HE'S FUNNY.

27:46.205 --> 27:49.168
HE'S JUST SUSCEPTIBLE TO BAD
THINGS, BAD CHOICES, BAD KIDS.

27:51.130 --> 27:54.253
BRETT WOULD HAVE CALLED THIS
HIS MOMENT.

27:54.253 --> 27:55.795
WHAT'S HIS MOMENT?

27:56.886 --> 27:59.929
HE CALLED IT --
HE CALLED IT THE MOMENT --

27:59.929 --> 28:03.142
WHEN A KID WOULD
BACK THEMSELVES INTO A CORNER,

28:03.142 --> 28:04.764
WHEN IT WOULD HIT THE FAN
SO BAD,

28:04.764 --> 28:06.936
THAT THERE'S NO OTHER CHOICE
BUT TO TURN IT AROUND,

28:06.936 --> 28:08.017
WIND UP IN LOCKUP, OR DEAD.

28:11.941 --> 28:16.025
BRETT WOULD SAY, "THAT'S WHEN
YOU CAN GET THEM, DAN.

28:16.025 --> 28:20.239
THAT'S WHEN
YOU CAN TURN THEM AROUND."

28:20.239 --> 28:22.531
AND THIS WOULD HAVE BEEN IT
FOR JARED.

28:25.244 --> 28:27.666
AND BRETT WOULD HAVE BEEN HERE
TO HELP.

28:35.424 --> 28:39.298
SO, DEREK'S BACK.

28:39.298 --> 28:42.011
IS THAT A QUESTION?

28:42.011 --> 28:43.763
NO, IT'S JUST...

28:43.763 --> 28:47.556
AND I'M GLAD, I AM,
FOR YOU AND THE KIDS,

28:47.556 --> 28:49.518
AND I DON'T WANT
TO MAKE THIS ALL ABOUT ME.

28:49.518 --> 28:50.900
IT'S JUST --

28:50.900 --> 28:54.854
HE SAYS HE WANTS TO COME BACK
AND JUST WORK -- FOR ME.

28:54.854 --> 28:57.116
STILL NOT SURE
WHAT YOU'RE ASKING.

28:57.116 --> 29:00.069
WELL, I'M ASKING
SHOULD I BELIEVE THAT?

29:00.069 --> 29:01.740
CAN I BELIEVE THAT?

29:01.740 --> 29:04.203
I DO.
YOU DO.

29:04.203 --> 29:05.414
YEAH, HE'S DIFFERENT.

29:05.414 --> 29:07.166
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO EXPLAIN IT,

29:07.166 --> 29:11.580
BUT...I THINK HE REALIZES
WHAT MAKES HIM HAPPY,

29:11.580 --> 29:13.793
AND HE'S CHOOSING IT.

29:13.793 --> 29:16.215
AND THAT MAKES ME HAPPY.

29:16.215 --> 29:19.178
I THINK
THIS IS HIS MOMENT.

29:19.178 --> 29:20.299
GREY,
WHAT DID YOU CALL ME FOR?

29:20.299 --> 29:22.181
'CAUSE IF YOU JUST WANT
TO YELL AT ME SOME MORE...

29:22.181 --> 29:23.222
NOPE.

29:23.222 --> 29:25.224
I THINK I JUST GOT THAT KID
HIS LIVER.

29:25.224 --> 29:27.306
WH...

29:31.981 --> 29:37.526
♪ WAS THERE NOTHING
BUT THE HUSH OF NIGHT? ♪

29:37.526 --> 29:41.200
JARED IS PREPPED AND READY,
STILL IN O.R. SIX.

29:41.200 --> 29:42.862
THANK YOU.

29:42.862 --> 29:44.403
AND THANK YOU,
OFFICER GIBSON.

29:44.403 --> 29:47.076
[ SIGHS ]

29:47.076 --> 29:49.618
HERE'S YOUR SECOND CHANCE,
JARED.

29:49.618 --> 29:56.916
♪ DID YOU FLEE
FROM WHAT WAS SAID AND SEEN? ♪

29:56.916 --> 29:59.418
♪ OH, MY LORD ♪

29:59.418 --> 30:03.092
♪ WON'T YOU PLEASE TELL ME WHY ♪

30:03.092 --> 30:08.187
♪ FAITH BESTOWS POWER? ♪

30:08.187 --> 30:11.230
OKAY,
FIRST KIDNEY IS OUT.

30:12.141 --> 30:19.698
♪ WAS THERE NOTHING
BUT THE HUSH OF NIGHT? ♪

30:21.110 --> 30:27.156
♪ HAD A TREASURE
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHERE ♪

30:29.408 --> 30:36.045
♪ DID YOU FLEE
FROM WHAT WAS SAID AND SEEN? ♪

30:41.510 --> 30:47.887
♪ YES, THE GOOD
WAS NOT WITHOUT THE BAD ♪

30:47.887 --> 30:52.641
♪ RAISE YOUR SWORD AND SHIELD ♪

30:56.775 --> 31:02.982
♪ YES, THE GOOD
WAS NOT WITHOUT THE BAD ♪

31:02.982 --> 31:08.077
♪ RAISE UP
YOUR SWORD AND SHIELD ♪

31:09.828 --> 31:12.661
♪ MM ♪

31:12.661 --> 31:15.374
[ SIREN WAILS ]

31:20.759 --> 31:22.881
Woman on P.A.:
JULIE HAMILTON, JULIE HAMILTON,

31:22.881 --> 31:25.134
PLEASE REPORT TO
ANY HOSPITAL PERSONNEL
MEMBER IMMEDIATELY.

31:25.134 --> 31:26.926
Meredith: YOU SEE THAT?

31:26.926 --> 31:28.057
YEAH.
THAT'S REALLY...

31:28.057 --> 31:29.178
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:35.064 --> 31:36.605
Derek:
WELL, THERE YOU ARE.

31:40.319 --> 31:42.571
AM I IN TROUBLE?

31:43.652 --> 31:48.077
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE NOT REALLY
SUPPOSED TO BE UP HERE.

31:48.077 --> 31:50.409
I SAW THAT MAN
IN THE E.R.

31:50.409 --> 31:52.031
HE WAS BLEEDING.

31:52.031 --> 31:55.204
YEAH, THE DOCTORS WORKED
REALLY HARD TO TRY TO SAVE HIM.

31:55.204 --> 31:56.335
BUT HE DIED.

31:56.335 --> 31:59.168
SO THEY'RE TAKING
ALL HIS PARTS OUT?

31:59.168 --> 32:01.000
MM-HMM.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.041
HE'S A DONOR,

32:02.041 --> 32:04.883
SO HIS BODY
IS GONNA HELP SAVE LIVES

32:04.883 --> 32:07.346
OF PEOPLE WHO NEED ORGANS
TO LIVE.

32:07.346 --> 32:10.719
MY GRANDPA
HAD A HEART TRANSPLANT ONCE.

32:10.719 --> 32:14.223
WILL SHE GIVE HIS HEART
TO SOMEONE ELSE?

32:14.223 --> 32:15.934
YES, SHE WILL.

32:15.934 --> 32:18.057
I WANT TO DO THAT.

32:18.057 --> 32:20.689
BE A DONOR?
NO.

32:20.689 --> 32:21.820
THE DOCTOR.

32:21.820 --> 32:24.483
I WANT TO DO
WHAT SHE'S DOING.

32:24.483 --> 32:26.235
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:26.235 --> 32:28.527
THAT'S MY WIFE.
SEE THE LEAD SURGEON?

32:28.527 --> 32:31.160
AND RIGHT NOW
SHE'S MAKING SURE

32:31.160 --> 32:33.072
THAT THE ARTERY
TO THE KIDNEY

32:33.072 --> 32:35.784
IS LONG ENOUGH
TO ATTACH TO SOMEONE ELSE.

32:35.784 --> 32:38.998
HOW DID SHE LEARN
ALL OF THAT?

32:38.998 --> 32:42.171
SHE WENT TO SCHOOL A LOT
AND PRACTICED.

32:42.171 --> 32:43.842
AND SHE'S JUST...

32:45.584 --> 32:47.716
...REALLY GREAT.

32:47.716 --> 32:49.468
YEAH.

32:49.468 --> 32:52.931
I THINK
THAT'S WHAT I WANT TO BE.

32:55.014 --> 32:56.595
FEELS GOOD,
DOESN'T IT?

32:56.595 --> 32:58.807
KNOWING WHAT
YOU WANT TO DO NEXT.

33:02.811 --> 33:03.812
[ GASPS ]

33:03.812 --> 33:05.154
THANK GOD, JULIE!

33:05.154 --> 33:07.156
OH!

33:07.156 --> 33:08.777
[ SIGHS ]

33:08.777 --> 33:12.371
MM. HEY, BABY.

33:22.791 --> 33:24.583
THAT BOY'S ALIVE?

33:24.583 --> 33:27.216
Meredith: HE IS.

33:27.216 --> 33:28.887
BECAUSE OF MY SON?

33:28.887 --> 33:34.433
THAT BOY AND THE 37 OTHERS
THAT WERE IN THE BANK TODAY --

33:34.433 --> 33:38.397
37 PEOPLE GOT TO GO HOME
TO THEIR FAMILIES TODAY

33:38.397 --> 33:40.139
BECAUSE OF YOUR SONS.

33:40.139 --> 33:44.273
NOW, I WOULD HAVE CALLED THAT
A PRETTY GOOD DAY'S WORK.

33:44.273 --> 33:45.774
BUT, GREY...

33:45.774 --> 33:49.568
THIS IS A LIST OF 100 PEOPLE
WHO ALL GOT SECOND CHANCES TODAY

33:49.568 --> 33:50.819
BECAUSE OF YOUR SONS.

33:50.819 --> 33:52.781
NOW, THEY WON'T KNOW
WHO TO THANK,

33:52.781 --> 33:56.365
SO I WOULD LIKE TO SAY
THANK YOU.

33:59.208 --> 34:01.039
[ Voice breaking ]
THEY WERE GOOD BOYS.

34:09.128 --> 34:10.048
[ SIREN WAILING ]

34:10.048 --> 34:12.171
OKAY, HERE WE ARE.

34:12.171 --> 34:15.224
I'LL JUST
PUT ON THE BRAKES.

34:15.224 --> 34:17.266
ALL RIGHT.

34:17.266 --> 34:20.018
OKAY, READY?
ONE, TWO, THREE.

34:20.018 --> 34:21.140
[ GROANS ]

34:21.140 --> 34:22.391
OH. GOOD.

34:27.356 --> 34:28.817
ALL RIGHT, LOOKS GOOD.

34:28.817 --> 34:30.149
USE THE CRUTCHES.

34:30.149 --> 34:32.191
I KNOW YOU WON'T THINK
YOU NEED THEM, BUT DO IT.

34:32.191 --> 34:33.242
IT'LL HEAL FASTER.

34:33.242 --> 34:36.365
THANK YOU, DR. TORRES.

34:36.365 --> 34:38.367
FOR EVERYTHING.

34:38.367 --> 34:40.038
OH, I'M --
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:40.038 --> 34:42.701
I'M SO SORRY ABOUT YOUR FRIENDS,
OFFICER PRUITT.

34:42.701 --> 34:44.082
THANKS.

34:44.082 --> 34:46.965
HEY, LISTEN, UM...

34:46.965 --> 34:48.917
YEAH?

34:48.917 --> 34:50.549
NEVER MIND.

34:50.549 --> 34:53.302
NO, NO, NO.
WHAT IS IT?

34:53.302 --> 34:59.178
WELL, IT'S JUST
THAT IF TODAY WEREN'T...

34:59.178 --> 35:00.559
TODAY.

35:00.559 --> 35:05.774
IF IT WAS ANY OTHER DAY,
LIKE, YOU KNOW, A REGULAR DAY,

35:05.774 --> 35:07.896
I'D ASK YOU IF YOU'D LIKE
TO HAVE DINNER WITH ME.

35:11.780 --> 35:14.153
IT'S LIKE --
IT'S LIKE I SAID, YOU KNOW,

35:14.153 --> 35:17.075
I JUST NEEDED SOMETHING
TO COME OUT OF THIS DAY RIGHT.

35:25.624 --> 35:31.590
UM, WELL, I WILL NEED
TO SEE YOU BACK HERE

35:31.590 --> 35:36.595
IN, UM, 10 DAYS
FOR A FOLLOW-UP ON THAT LEG.

35:38.677 --> 35:41.430
10 DAYS?

35:41.430 --> 35:42.971
IS THAT ALL RIGHT?

35:42.971 --> 35:46.185
SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN.

35:46.185 --> 35:49.228
THAT IS A PLAN.

35:49.228 --> 35:53.031
ALL RIGHT.
SEE YOU IN 10 DAYS.

35:56.074 --> 35:57.075
HMM.

35:59.698 --> 36:02.581
[ SIGHS ] NICK.

36:02.581 --> 36:04.283
HEY.
DR. EDWARDS.

36:04.283 --> 36:05.584
GLAD I GET THE CHANCE
TO SAY GOODBYE.

36:05.584 --> 36:06.835
BETTER MAKE IT QUICK,
THOUGH.

36:06.835 --> 36:07.996
I'M NOT LETTING THIS KID
OUT OF MY SIGHT AGAIN.

36:07.996 --> 36:09.087
OH, SON OF A --

36:09.087 --> 36:11.750
WAIT, WAIT, HANG ON.
BEFORE YOU RUN OFF.

36:11.750 --> 36:15.464
UH, I COULD BE
TOTALLY OFF BASE HERE,

36:15.464 --> 36:18.427
BUT YOU AND I
MAYBE HAD S--

36:18.427 --> 36:20.639
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:20.639 --> 36:22.681
HMM.

36:22.681 --> 36:25.143
WOULD YOU LIKE TO MAYBE
HANG OUT SOMETIME?

36:25.143 --> 36:26.975
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

36:26.975 --> 36:29.067
WAIT, REALLY?

36:29.067 --> 36:32.150
YEAH, YEAH, I MEAN --
I MEAN, YOU'D REALLY WANT TO?

36:32.150 --> 36:34.072
YEAH. [ LAUGHS ]
I WOULD.

36:34.072 --> 36:36.615
UH, WE COULD GRAB A DRINK
OR SOMETHING.

36:36.615 --> 36:37.986
OH, I-I CAN'T DRINK.
I'M...

36:37.986 --> 36:39.117
OH, OKAY. THEN COFFEE.

36:39.117 --> 36:41.580
COFFEE'S GREAT.

36:41.580 --> 36:43.081
YEAH, I'M ALL ABOUT
THE COFFEE.

36:43.081 --> 36:44.122
[ LAUGHS ] PERFECT.
COOL.

36:44.122 --> 36:44.993
WELL,
I'M FREE FRIDAY NIGHT.

36:44.993 --> 36:46.495
[ SCOFFS ]

36:46.495 --> 36:49.878
I-I CAN'T.
FRIDAY'S THE JUNIOR PROM.

36:49.878 --> 36:51.500
YOU CHAPERONE
HIGH-SCHOOL EVENTS, TOO?

36:51.500 --> 36:53.592
NO, I-I GO TO THEM.

36:56.044 --> 36:57.886
[ LAUGHS ]

36:57.886 --> 37:00.138
17 YEARS OLD?!

37:00.138 --> 37:02.100
COULD YOU MAYBE
NOT SCREAM IT LIKE THAT?

37:02.100 --> 37:04.263
[ Laughing ] OH, MY GOD.
I CAN'T -- I CAN'T BREATHE.

37:04.263 --> 37:05.604
OH!

37:05.604 --> 37:08.307
I KNOW I TOLD YOU
TO EXPAND YOUR HORIZONS,

37:08.307 --> 37:09.308
BUT OH, MY --

37:09.308 --> 37:11.310
IT WAS
HIS LITTLE SISTER'S CLASS.

37:11.310 --> 37:16.275
HE SAID HE WAS DOING THIS
TEACHER-HELPER-VOLUNTEER THING.

37:16.275 --> 37:20.909
THOUGHT IT WOULD LOOK GOOD
ON HIS COLLEGE APPLICATIONS.

37:20.909 --> 37:23.161
[ LAUGHS ]

37:23.161 --> 37:25.994
I'M GONNA NEED
MANY MORE OF THESE.

37:25.994 --> 37:29.077
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

37:34.172 --> 37:36.214
HEY.

37:36.214 --> 37:37.586
THANKS FOR DOING THIS
FOR ME.

37:37.586 --> 37:41.219
THESE TWO WILL LOOK
AS GOOD AS THEY POSSIBLY CAN

37:41.219 --> 37:44.803
BEFORE THEIR MOTHER
SEES THEM ONE LAST TIME.

37:46.805 --> 37:50.979
THOUGH, IT'S TAKING
A LITTLE LONGER THAN I EXPECTED.

37:50.979 --> 37:51.980
YOU OKAY?

37:51.980 --> 37:53.812
YEAH.

37:53.812 --> 37:55.394
YEAH?

37:55.394 --> 37:57.776
YEAH. I'M FINE.

38:00.359 --> 38:03.952
THIS IS TOTALLY SOMETHING
SLOAN WOULD'VE DONE.

38:03.952 --> 38:06.034
REALLY?
YEAH.

38:06.034 --> 38:08.367
YOU KNOW, HE REALLY DID
TREAT ME LIKE A SON.

38:08.367 --> 38:09.998
PASSED EVERYTHING ON.

38:09.998 --> 38:13.121
HE GOT SUCH A CHARGE OUT IT,
THE PLASTICS POSSE.

38:13.121 --> 38:14.873
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

38:14.873 --> 38:18.296
IT GOT A LITTLE GOOFY SOMETIMES,
HONESTLY, BUT...
MM-HMM.

38:18.296 --> 38:20.128
I WANT TO DO THAT.

38:20.128 --> 38:24.723
YOU KNOW, PASS IT ON TO SOMEONE,
THE WAY HE DID FOR ME.

38:24.723 --> 38:26.014
WHATEVER.

38:26.014 --> 38:28.186
I DON'T KNOW
IF I'M MAKING ANY SENSE.

38:32.140 --> 38:34.353
IT MAKES
A LOT OF SENSE.

38:37.776 --> 38:39.067
YEAH.

38:39.067 --> 38:44.363
♪ THE LORD OF LIFE
STOLE YOU AWAY FROM ME ♪

38:44.363 --> 38:46.655
♪ HE FILLED YOUR CUP ♪

38:46.655 --> 38:51.209
♪ IT OVERFLOWED
THE WINE OF THE SEA ♪

38:51.209 --> 38:53.452
WHEW.
IT'S COLD OUT HERE.

38:53.452 --> 38:54.793
IT'S QUIET OUT HERE.

38:54.793 --> 38:56.214
MM.

38:56.214 --> 38:59.878
EVER SINCE YOU'VE BEEN BACK,
YOU GUYS HAVE BEEN RECONNECTING.

38:59.878 --> 39:01.510
[ LAUGHS ]
VIGOROUSLY.

39:01.510 --> 39:04.012
YOU SHOULD HAVE BUILT
THICKER WALLS.

39:04.012 --> 39:05.093
[ SIGHS ]

39:05.093 --> 39:06.134
YOU OKAY?

39:07.225 --> 39:09.928
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

39:09.928 --> 39:11.970
I DIDN'T WANT TO ASK YOU,

39:11.970 --> 39:14.853
AND I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO
BIG-BROTHER YOU.

39:14.853 --> 39:17.065
AND YOU DON'T NEED ME TO.

39:18.146 --> 39:22.190
THERE WAS A ROBBERY,
TWO SHOOTINGS,

39:22.190 --> 39:25.694
AND YOU DECLARED
TWO MEN DEAD.

39:25.694 --> 39:28.657
I KEPT THINKING
ABOUT DAD.

39:28.657 --> 39:32.040
I WANTED TO KNOW
IF YOU'RE OKAY.

39:35.874 --> 39:37.916
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.

39:37.916 --> 39:40.879
THAT YOU'RE BACK.

39:40.879 --> 39:43.051
THAT YOU'RE
MAKING IT WORK.

39:43.051 --> 39:44.963
THAT YOU'RE NOT RUNNING.

39:44.963 --> 39:47.215
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"RUNNING"?

39:47.215 --> 39:49.057
HEY,
I AM NOT JUDGING.

39:49.057 --> 39:51.930
WE ARE RUNNERS.

39:51.930 --> 39:54.813
I RAN FROM MY ENGAGEMENT.
YOU RAN FROM ADDISON.

39:56.144 --> 39:57.976
I THINK...

39:57.976 --> 40:00.148
AFTER DAD...

40:02.150 --> 40:06.655
...IF SOMETHING SCARES US,
WE SPRINT FAST AS WE CAN.

40:09.027 --> 40:12.581
BUT YOU TURNED AROUND
THIS TIME.

40:12.581 --> 40:14.372
THAT'S SOMETHING.

40:14.372 --> 40:15.994
I'M INSPIRED.

40:15.994 --> 40:18.376
Meredith: OPEN YOUR EYES.

40:18.376 --> 40:20.629
TAKE A GOOD LOOK AROUND YOU.

40:20.629 --> 40:22.380
DID MOM TELL YOU
I WENT TO GO SEE HER?

40:22.380 --> 40:23.922
NO.

40:23.922 --> 40:26.174
WOW.
HOW DID THAT GO?

40:26.174 --> 40:30.178
SHE SAID I WAS TIRED
AND MISERABLE, WHICH I WAS.

40:30.178 --> 40:31.810
[ LAUGHS ]

40:31.810 --> 40:33.141
TOLD ME
TO GET IT TOGETHER.

40:33.141 --> 40:34.182
[ SIGHS ]
NO SYMPATHY.

40:34.182 --> 40:36.555
OH, NO, NEVER.

40:36.555 --> 40:40.899
SHE SAID, "DEREK, TAKE A GOOD,
HARD LOOK AT YOUR LIFE.

40:40.899 --> 40:44.152
IF IT'S NOT WORKING,
SHUT UP AND FIX IT."

40:44.152 --> 40:45.153
[ LAUGHS ]

40:45.153 --> 40:47.155
HOW'S THE VIEW?

40:47.155 --> 40:51.029
DO YOU LIKE WHAT YOU SEE?

40:51.029 --> 40:55.283
AMY, I'VE BEEN MISSING OUT
ON EVERYTHING IN MY LIFE.

40:55.283 --> 41:00.208
I MEAN, I'M WATCHING MY KIDS
GROW UP ON A COMPUTER.

41:00.208 --> 41:02.751
I DON'T WANT TO MISS
MY FAMILY.

41:02.751 --> 41:05.584
I DON'T WANT TO MISS
ANOTHER SECOND.

41:05.584 --> 41:08.426
I WANT TO COACH SOCCER,
GO TO BALLET RECITALS.

41:08.426 --> 41:13.051
I DON'T NEED TO CHANGE
THE WORLD.

41:13.051 --> 41:16.975
CLIPPING ANEURYSMS,
STOPPING BLEEDS --

41:16.975 --> 41:18.977
THAT'S THE FUN.

41:18.977 --> 41:21.560
THAT'S CHANGING THE WORLD
WITH OUR HANDS.

41:23.522 --> 41:26.945
THINK BACK AGAIN
TO WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE.

41:26.945 --> 41:30.569
WHEN DID THAT STOP
BEING ENOUGH?

41:30.569 --> 41:32.370
SAVING SOMEONE'S LIFE?

41:32.370 --> 41:34.613
ARE YOU LIVING THE LIFE
YOU PICTURED FOR YOURSELF?

41:34.613 --> 41:36.034
THAT'S MORE THAN ENOUGH.

41:42.170 --> 41:44.002
I'M GLAD YOU'RE BACK.

41:44.002 --> 41:46.294
ME TOO.

41:53.511 --> 41:55.934
I THINK I'M FALLING IN LOVE
WITH OWEN HUNT.

41:57.185 --> 42:02.060
AND I'M REALLY AFRAID
THAT IT'S GONNA DESTROY ME.

42:05.944 --> 42:08.647
IT WOULDN'T BE LOVE
IF IT DIDN'T.

42:08.647 --> 42:12.951
[ OWL HOOTING ]

42:12.951 --> 42:14.653
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

42:14.653 --> 42:17.656
OR ARE YOU STILL DREAMING
OF SOMETHING EVEN BIGGER?
